fields.alert_text: Metric type II burst frequency drift from 45 MHz (02:31 UT)  to 20 MHz (02:37 UT).
fields.comment:
Gopalswamy 2016 (https://iopscience.iop.org/article/10.3847/1538-4357/833/2/216/pdf)
For a behind-the-limb event, emission likely to be in the harmonic component because foreground plasma would absorb the fundamental. This means the plasma frequency at the source region when the type II burst started was ~22.5 MHz.
